title: Black Country comedian Sean Percival to headline gig
text:
Sean Percival, a former Dudley welder, who also writes comedy scripts, will perform his stand-up act at Sadlers Brewhouse and Bar on the Conyers Trading Estate, Station Drive. 
He will have drinkers in fits of laughter on November 25 from 8pm. 
Sean’s brand of comedy confronts realism in an explosively funny way. 
His act is down to earth but full of attitude. 
Also appearing will be Michael Crump, who starred in Lenny Henry’s recent comedy drama Danny and the Human Zoo, Stuart Woodings and Neil Irving. What do you think?
